threads.title: A1465 820-00164 no power
threads.message:
Hi,

I have an A1465 820-00164 that has green light, but no fan spin, no usb activity, and no voltage on cpu coils, and puls 100mA from bench PSU.

It seams the Q8150 has already been replaced before. I get 0.100V on ALL_SYS_PWRGD.

Can you help?

threads.title: A1465 820-00164 no power
threads.message: W/O  Q8150  i get 3.3V on  ALL_SYS_PWRGD

threads.title: A1465 820-00164 no power
threads.message:
CPU gets power now?
You can leave out Q8150.

threads.title: A1465 820-00164 no power
threads.message:
Yes it does, and now I have boot.

With other Q8150 it doesn't boot and i don't get  ALL_SYS_PWRGD  high. Is it safe to leave it out? No function gets lost?

threads.title: A1465 820-00164 no power
threads.message:
Q8150 isn't the issue.
You have problem with one resistor divider from its inputs.
You can leave it as is; Q8150 is a redundant protection.
